-- ARGENTINE DAYBOOK: Fernandez Announces Province’s Debt Plan
-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 2011-12-29T03:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/argentine-daybook-fernandez-announces-province-s-debt-plan.html
Argentina ’s President Cristina
Fernandez de Kirchner, who will undergo surgery on Jan. 4 for
thyroid cancer, yesterday announced a plan to refinance the debt
of 17 provinces.  In her first public appearance after the announcement of
her illness, Fernandez yesterday said that 17 provinces will cut
servicing costs by about 40 percent and the government extended
the grace period on the debt to December 2013 from December
2011.  WHAT TO WATCH:  *  Central bank  is scheduled to release its 2012 monetary program
that will be sent to Congress.  ECONOMY/COMMODITIES:  * The national statistics agency releases November’s
construction activity report at 4 p.m. local time.  * The Buenos Aires Cereals Exchange releases its weekly crop
report in the afternoon.  EQUITIES:  * The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index yesterday fell 1.3 percent to 2,425.98, led
by  Petroleo Brasileiro SA , which dropped 3.2 percent to 57.5
pesos.  MARKETS:  * The peso fell 0.1 percent 4.3026 per dollar. The currency has
declined 7.5 percent against the dollar this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
